Fearful lest his work should assume the character of a chronicle, he fell into the opposite extreme, and frequently relatoe circumstances without stating the exact year in which they occurred. He did this either in imitation of the Roman writers, or for the purpose of avoidiug the difficulty of fixing each transaction to a par- ticular year, there being such frequent discre- pancies on those points in the sources whence he derived his information.
